
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-cantor-ietf-kitten-saml-ec-01.txt'>
    <title>"SAML Enhanced Client SASL and GSS-API Mechanisms", Scott Cantor, Simon Josefsson</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-cantor-ietf-kitten-saml-ec-01.txt</link>
    <description>Security Assertion Markup Language (SAML) 2.0 is a generalized framework for the exchange of security-related information between asserting and relying parties.  Simple Authentication and Security Layer (SASL) and the Generic Security Service Application Program Interface (GSS-API) are application frameworks to facilitate an extensible authentication model.  This document specifies a SASL and GSS-API mechanism for SAML 2.0 that leverages the capabilities of a SAML-aware "enhanced client" to address significant barriers to federated authentication in a manner that encourages reuse of existing SAML bindings and profiles designed for non-browser scenarios.</description>
    <dc:date>2011-02-28T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
